<HEADLINE>
Police: Nebraska mall gunman ' s victims included 6 employees, 2
customers
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OMAHA, Nebraska 2007-12-06 16:38:51 UTC
</P>
<P>
The teenage gunman who went on a shooting rampage in a department
store may have smuggled an assault rifle into the mall underneath
clothing, Omaha police said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Omaha Police Chief Thomas Warren said the young man "appeared to
be concealing something balled up in hooded sweat shirt" on a
surveillance video.
</P>
<P>
As gunshots rang out over Christmas music, those at the mall
huddled in dressing rooms and barricaded themselves in offices as
the shooter, 19-year-old Robert A. Hawkins, sprayed the third
floor of Von Maur with gunfire.
</P>
<P>
Police identified Hawkins' victims as six employees and two
customers.
</P>
<P>
The customers killed were Gary Scharf of Lincoln, Nebraska, and
John McDonald of Iowa, police said. The employees killed were
Angie Schuster, Maggie Webb, Janet Jorgensen, Diane Trent, Gary
Joy and Beverly Flynn.
</P>
